President Obama has nominated Michael Kenny O'Keefe and Robert Okun to serve on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. O'Keefe is a sole practitioner with experience in criminal defense and family law. He has represented individuals in over 2,000 cases and litigated over 200 trials. He has also worked as an adjunct professor of law at the University of Baltimore School of Law. Okun is currently the Chief of the Special Proceedings Division of the U.S. Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia. He has also served as an Executive Assistant U.S. Attorney and as Special Counsel to the U.S. Attorney for Professional Development and Legal Policy. Okun has experience in various areas of law, including consumer litigation and fraud. President Obama believes that both nominees have demonstrated a strong commitment to justice and integrity throughout their careers.